article.description: Emani Gant and Kavin Gilder-Tilbury combined for 31 points as Texas State defeated Interstate 35 rival UTSA 76-53 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Texas State runs away from UTSA Roadrunners 76-53
article.linkText: Texas State runs away from UTSA Roadrunners 76-53
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- Emani Gant and Kavin Gilder-Tilbury combined for 31 points as Texas State defeated Interstate 35 rival UTSA 76-53 on Wednesday night. Gant led the scoring with 16 points on 6-for-12 shooting with three steals, Gilder-Tilbury scored 15 points and dished a career-high six assists. Cameron Naylor added 14 points for the Bobcats (3-1) and Anthony Roberson chipped in 10. Ethan Montalvo tied the school record with eight steals. Texas State closed the first half on a 10-0 run over the final 4:30, going into the break ahead 39-21. UTSA (1-7) only got a single, missed, shot off in that span, while making five turnovers. It was more of the same after intermission as Texas State opened with an 8-0 run, building the lead to 47-21 in 90 seconds. The Roadrunners made 26 turnovers while Texas State had 14 steals and blocked five shots. Ryan Bowie led UTSA with 11 points and 11 rebounds.
